  .content#faq
    .text
      h2 Ski Trip FAQ
      p.question Can I bring my non Imperial friends?
      p.answer <strong>Yes</strong> - however they need to get associate membership of the union, which is &pound;4 per month so they just need to get it for December, as well as club membership. https://www.imperialcollegeunion.org/your-union/how-were-run/membership
      p.question When is the booking deadline?
      p.answer Midnight 8th November
      p.question Do I need my own skis or snowboard and related equipment?
      p.answer Skis/boots/poles/snowboards are not required - you can book them using NUCO's booking system. To see the prices go on the booking system and you can see them listed, there are various different grades of equipment.
      p.question Do I need my own outerwear (jacket, salopettes, gloves, goggles etc)?
      p.answer These can also be selected for rental, when booking the trip.
      p.question Can I bring my own skis/board?
      p.answer Yes you can however the space on the coaches is limited so the space needs to be selected when booking and there are a limited number of people who can select this option.
      p.question If I provide my own transport is there a reduction in base price?
      p.answer If you make your own way there and back then the price is reduced by &pound;40. However if you only take the coach one way, for example the coach there and then make your own way home, there is no reduction.
